<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402249>
    dc:description "FIGURE 12. Antipathes sp. specimen INV.131338. (a) Colony photographed in situ. (b) Spread-out colony showing the curved branches and the arrangement of the branchlets. The red dots represent the fusion points of branchlets belonging to the branch indicated by the red arrow. (c) Section of a branch 0.16 mm in diameter. (d) Section of a branch 0.36 mm in diameter. (e) Section of a branch 0.50 mm in diameter. (f) Section of a branch 0.80 mm in diameter. (g–j) Shapes of the spines." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4402249/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

